 The Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps in Delta State has arrested 19 suspects for allegedly being in possession of illegally refined fuel. The NSCDC Public Relations Officer in the state, Emeka Peters, disclosed this in a statement made available to the News Agency of Nigeria, on Sunday, in Asaba. The statement quoted Akinsanya Abiodun, Commandant of the NSCDC, Delta State, as saying that two tankers and seven trucks were impounded alongside the 19 apprehended suspects. It stressed that two of the suspects were arrested by the Anti-Vandal Unit of the command in Patani Local Government Area of the state on March 9. The statement added that the duo were conveying kerosene suspected to have been illegally refined in polythene bags inside a Mercedes 817 truck. It stated that the 17 other suspects were nabbed at Ozoro, the headquarters of Isoko North LGA, for being in possession of diesel suspected to have also been illegally refined. The 17 suspects, according to the statement, were nabbed by the commandâ€™s Intelligence Squad. It further quoted the Commandant as saying that the fight against pipeline vandalism, crude oil theft, general vandalism and other criminality, had been intensified in the state. It then warned criminals and those described as enemies of the state to either repent or relocate from the state. The statement read that after investigation, the suspects would be charged to court to serve as deterrent to others. (NAN). 